This paper presents a method for efficient implementation of sparse logistic regression, which is a common technique in machine learning and data analysis. The paper focuses on the computational challenges of high-dimensional data, which suggests that it is likely to be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses experimental results, which suggests that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.ST (Statistics).
